noun.description: A coming out, an emergence; the departure of a person from a place; an opening, a place for coming out.
An event; a result or product.

adjective.description: That comes or will come out; that issues forth.

origin: Middle English; earliest use found in Ancrene Riwle. From out- + come + -ing, after to come out<br>late 18th century; earliest use found in George Culley (bap. 1735, d. 1813), agriculturist. From out- + coming, after to come out.
